I was diagnosed with hyperthyroidism November, 2015. I gained over 10kg in one month around December 2015 (yes, I know) from taking methimazole (to control thyroid hormone production. Hairloss, acne, and weight gain happened in a short amount of time, and I never had these problema prior to my thyroid issues. I got radio active iodine therapy around June 2016. I was advised to stay at home and isolate for one month. I lost weight during my isolation because the only thing I ate mas mostly bread and peanut butter because I had no appetite at all. After that, I became hypothyroid since my thyroid gland was taken out through RAI. Ever since then, I have been taking levothyroxine for supplementation. It was a wild ride, if my levels weren't right, my energy levels would plummet and experience hairfall (I lost 50% of my hair). I tried mitigating my issues through major lifestyle changes. I went pescatarian 4 years ago, I cut dairy, sugary foods, and processed foods and incorporated exercise daily. Through this and getting the right levothyroxine dosage, I was able to control my hormones. As a result, I never felt healthier. I am fit now, if I wasn't diagnosed with hyperthyroidism, I don't think I will have a major lifestyle change. It took me years to adjust my lifestyle to cater to my thyroid issues, but it was worth it.
